// SOURCE: Source Files/Intergrations/Fusion Intergrations 2/Fusion Forge/Product Guide.txt
// NOTE: Integrated into the Fusion FSN tree for migration traceability.
// CONTENT:
// Product Guide: Fusion Forge1. Architecture: The MetabuilderForge is not a compiler itself; it is a Compiler Orchestrator.The Build PipelineGraph Resolution: Forge parses Fusion.toml and builds a Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG) of all components.Environment Isolation: It creates a "Sandbox" (.forge/) where it sets up a virtualenv for Python, a node_modules for JS, and a target dir for Rust/C++.CodeGen: It scans for cross-language calls (e.g., Rust calling Python) and generates the necessary FFI boilerplate.Parallel Execution: It invokes cargo, clang, etc., in parallel where the graph allows.Linking: It statically links compiled objects into a single executable or WASM module.2. Roadmapv1.0 (Now): Support for Rust, C++, Python, JS. Local build caching.v1.5: "Fusion Remote Builds" - Offload compilation to a build cluster (distributed sccache).v2.0: "Language Fusion" - Inline multi-language support (e.g., writing Python directly inside a Rust file block).3. Integration with SupernovaForge is the only official way to build packages for the Supernova Runtime. It injects the specific runtime headers and compiles against the Supernova ABI (Application Binary Interface) automatically.
